# Urban Scene CNN

CNN model for classifying urban scenes using the MIT Places dataset subset.

## Setup & Run

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python urban_scene_cnn.py
```

## Dataset Structure

```
data/
  apartment_building/
  building_facade/
  crosswalk/
  office_building/
```

## Outputs

All results are saved in the `outputs/` folder:
- `sample_images.png` — one sample per class
- `training_curves.png` — loss & accuracy over epochs
- `confusion_matrix.png` — test set confusion matrix
- `per_class_accuracy_table.png` — per-class accuracy table
- `urban_cnn_model.pth` — saved model weights